      "text": "## Context (session background)\n- Comprehensive multi-agent heartbeat and backup architecture audit and optimization session\n- Created planner heartbeat cron job (30min, gemini-flash) and identified moltbook lacked keep-alive heartbeat\n- Generated main workspace weekly report covering AGENTS.md slimming (17K→13.4K), memory cleanup (90+→8 files), docs consolidation (48→34 files), and milestone tracking (03-17 through 03-23)\n- Discovered and fixed GitHub backup infrastructure: created missing repos `openclaw-memory` and `openclaw-subworkspaces`\n- Optimized subworkspace backup from conflicting single-branch pushes to branch-isolated architecture (`planner`/`moltbook` branches); deleted redundant `main` branch\n- Updated subworkspace backup cron payload to sequentially enter each subdirectory and push to its respective branch\n- Identified that all heartbeat sessions were `isolated`, defeating keep-alive purpose for agents without permanent channel entry\n- Executed 5 configuration changes: planner heartbeat `isolated`→`main`, moltbook new heartbeat created, planner total check 3h→6h, workspace compaction path fixed, moltbook HEARTBEAT.md simplified\n- Migrated heavy logic (desensitization rules, proactive notifications) from moltbook HEARTBEAT.md to AGENTS.md as permanent constraints\n- Restarted gateway; confirmed final state of all 16 cron jobs via direct `jobs.json` read\n- Clarified `isolated` vs `main` session distinction for heartbeat architecture\n\n## Decisions (durable)\n- Heartbeat session strategy: `session: main` for agents without permanent messaging channel (planner, moltbook); `session: isolated` for main (has Feishu private chat as permanent entry)\n- GitHub backup architecture: 4 repos — `openclaw-memory` (daily), `openclaw-workspace-config` (weekly), `openclaw-subworkspaces` with branch isolation (`planner`/`moltbook` branches), `openclaw-self-improving` (weekly)\n- Branch-isolated subworkspace backup: each sub-agent pushes to its own branch in `openclaw-subworkspaces`; `main` branch deleted to prevent mutual overwrites\n- Cron payload for subworkspace backup updated to sequential two-step push (planner then moltbook, each to its own branch)\n- moltbook heartbeat simplified to keep-alive only; behavioral rules migrated to AGENTS.md as permanent constraints\n- Planner total check frequency reduced from 3h to 6h to align with moltbook and reduce redundant overhead\n- Outdated workspace path `workspace-main` corrected to `workspace` in weekly compaction cron payload\n- Direct `jobs.json` modification used as reliable fallback when `openclaw cron edit` CLI is unstable\n\n## User model deltas (about the human)\n- User actively participates in architectural decisions, confirming changes before execution\n- User expects complete system diagnostics before optimization proposals\n- User values architectural clarity and asks for detailed explanations when logic is non-obvious\n- User manages 再回楼半山民宿 and relies on stable automated infrastructure\n\n## Agent model deltas (about the assistant/system)\n- `openclaw cron edit` proved unstable during session (gateway connection drops); direct `jobs.json` modification is the reliable fallback\n- `openclaw cron list --json` output polluted by doctor warnings; `jobs.json` direct read is the reliable parsing method\n- Confirmed `isolated` heartbeat sessions destroy context after execution, providing zero keep-alive benefit\n- moltbook HEARTBEAT.md previously mixed keep-alive with heavy logic (community interaction, daily/weekly summaries); migrated to AGENTS.md for permanent enforcement\n\n## Lessons & pitfalls (symptom / cause / fix / prevention)\n- Symptom: Subworkspace backup push failures Cause: `openclaw-subworkspaces` GitHub repo did not exist Fix: Created repo via `gh repo create` Prevention: Include repo existence verification in backup setup playbooks.\n- Symptom: Planner session unreachable despite active heartbeat Cause: `isolated` session target destroys context after each execution Fix: Changed heartbeat to `session: main` Prevention: Use `session: main` for any agent needing `sessions_send` reachability.\n- Symptom: Two subworkspace directories overwriting each other Cause: Both pushed to same branch of same repo Fix: Branch isolation (`planner`/`moltbook` branches) + sequential payload Prevention: Design multi-agent backup with branch isolation from the start.\n- Symptom: moltbook heartbeat contained heavy interaction logic Cause: HEARTBEAT.md mixed keep-alive with behavioral content Fix: Simplified to keep-alive only; migrated rules to AGENTS.md Prevention: Keep HEARTBEAT.md extremely thin; reserve logic for AGENTS.md or cron payloads.\n- Symptom: `cron list --json` produced malformed output Cause: Doctor warnings polluted the JSON stream Fix: Read `jobs.json` directly Prevention: Never rely on `cron list --json` for programmatic parsing.\n- Symptom: Gateway connection dropped during `cron edit` Cause: Internal reconnection triggered by cron operations Fix: Direct `jobs.json` modification bypasses gateway CLI instability Prevention: Use filesystem edits as fallback when gateway CLI is unstable.\n\n## Learning governance candidates (.learnings / promotion / skill extraction)\n### Entry 1\n**Priority**: medium\n**Status**: pending\n**Area**: infra\n### Summary\nPromote heartbeat session strategy pattern to collab-setup skill\n### Details\nThe `session: main` for non-entry agents + `session: isolated` for agents with permanent channels is a reusable architectural pattern.\n### Suggested Action\nAdd a \"Heartbeat Session Strategy\" section to the collab-setup skill documenting when to use `main` vs `isolated` for different agent types.\n\n### Entry 2\n**Priority**: low\n**Status**: pending\n**Area**: infra\n### Summary\nDocument branch-isolated multi-agent backup pattern\n### Details\nSingle repo with agent-specific branches for subworkspace backups minimizes repo sprawl while maintaining data integrity.\n### Suggested Action\nAdd this as the preferred architecture in docs/technical-knowledge.md or the backup playbook.\n\n## Open loops / next actions\n- Verify moltbook heartbeat triggers successfully at next interval (~11:40) and confirms session persistence\n- Confirm subworkspace backup cron executes correctly on next Sunday 03:00 with new branch-based payload\n- Monitor `Agent Reach Daily Check` for continued consecutive errors (delivery mode issue: \"Delivering to Feishu requires target\")\n- Monitor `主工作区精简与记忆蒸馏` for repeat delivery failure (\"⚠️ ✉️ Message failed\")\n\n## Retrieval tags / keywords\n- heartbeat-session-strategy\n- github-backup\n- branch-isolation\n- jobs-json\n- cron-optimization\n- moltbook-rules\n- session-main\n- session-isolated\n- planner\n- moltbook\n\n## Invariants\n- Always use `session: main` for heartbeat crons on agents without a permanent messaging channel entry\n- Always use `session: isolated` for heartbeat crons on agents with a permanent messaging channel\n- Always use branch isolation when multiple agents back up to the same repository\n- Prefer direct `jobs.json` reads over `cron list --json` for programmatic inspection\n- Keep HEARTBEAT.md files extremely thin; reserve behavioral logic for AGENTS.md or cron payloads\n\n## Derived\n- This run confirmed that `session: isolated` heartbeats provide zero keep-alive benefit; the switch to `session: main` was the single highest-impact fix for planner/moltbook reachability\n- Direct filesystem edits to `jobs.json` are the reliable fallback when `openclaw cron` CLI is unstable due to gateway connection issues\n- Migrating behavioral rules from HEARTBEAT.md to AGENTS.md makes them durable across all turn types, not just heartbeat cycles",
